commit.message: Bump and release 0.11.1
Fix formatting in 412dd3c55fa2f9efe096465c0976bd9aee3fd05d

Bugfix the run_task usage

The use_reloader argument is not used.
Support Quart 0.19.4 and the event_class

Fix tests

The nursery needs to be doing something to be cancelled otherwise it
will complete instead.

Fix documentation links

These have been incorrect since the switch to github.
Bump and release 0.11.0

Add a publish workflow

This will allow trusted publishing of Quart-Trio to PyPI.

Support Quart 0.19

This has required mostly small changes throughout.

Support Python 3.12 drop Python 3.7

Following a new release and recent end of life.
Fix typo in 639d59cfd631b97ed73991a38d693640c92e5726
Fix form response file saving
Support and test against Python 3.11

Update to pass CI

This has required updates to match changes in mypy and allowing the
docs to complete with warnings.

Note that tmp_path has replaced tmpdir for pytest.
Turn all MultiError occurrences into BaseExceptionGroup
Bump and release 0.10.0
Fix noqa for print
Update to support Quart 0.18.0
Fix missing websocket_received event in TrioASGIWebsocketConnection.handle_messages

Switch to github rather than gitlab

GitHub has a better pricing model and is more popular for OSS, hence
the move.

Add configuration for read the docs

This should, hopefully allow the docs to build and make it clearer to
other users how to setup and install the docs requirements.

Add a github workflow

This will allow the CI to run on github rather than gitlab, allowing
me to transfer.
Bump and release 0.9.1

Use trio-typing to improve the typing

This should result in fewer errors.
Bugfix use parsing lock when loading form data
Fix wrong lock class on TrioRequest
Fix issues with the latest mypy
Fix typo in 96d3bdf8515a5a2a8fecb8a79120932e3cfb6b44

Bugfix filter out cancelled errors from MultiErrors

If a CancelledError is present in the MultiError it should be raised
and the error not handled. As in this case the task has been cancelled
and hence there is no handling to be done.

Update the background task documentation

Based on the new API and support.
